│  encyclopedia In [fluid                                                     │
│  dynamics](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fluid_dynamics "Fluid dynamics"),  │
│  **dynamic pressure** (denoted by q or Q and sometimes called **velocity    │
│  pressure**) is the quantity defined                                        │
│  by:[[1]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dynamic_pressure#cite_note-LJC3.5-  │
│  1) ![Image 1: {\displaystyle q={\frac {1}{2}}\rho                          │
│  \,u^{2}}](https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/195e8de  │
│  fff286e108571af869f6af39158047771) where (in                               │
│  [SI](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/International_System_of_Units           │
│  "International System of Units") units): * q is the dynamic                │
│  [pressure](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pressure "Pressure") in           │
│  [pascals](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pascal_(unit) "Pascal (unit)")     │
│  (i.e., [N](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Newton_(unit) "Newton             │
│  (unit)")/[m](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Metre "Metre")2), * ρ (Greek    │
│  letter rho) is the fluid [mass                                             │
│  density](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mass_density "Mass density") (e.g.  │
